<!-- Q6: MULTIPLE REGRESSION -->
<div id="q6">
<div class="qblock"><div class="qnum">Q6</div><div><div class="qtitle">Multiple Regression</div><div class="qsub">Predict output from multiple input features · sklearn LinearRegression</div></div><span class="mbadge m4">4 Marks</span></div>
<div class="sec">📖 Concept</div>
<div class="understand"><div class="ul">What it means</div><p>Multiple regression predicts a continuous output (like house price) from multiple input features (like size, rooms, location). Unlike simple regression with one variable, multiple regression uses the formula: Y = β₀ + β₁X₁ + β₂X₂ + ... + βₙXₙ</p></div>
<div class="sec">💻 Python Program</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Multiple Regression — House Price Dataset</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<div class="code"># Multiple Regression in Python
# Dataset: House Price Prediction
# Features: Size(sqft), Bedrooms, Age(years) → Predicts: Price(lakhs)

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
