<!-- Q7: ID3 -->
<div id="q7">
<div class="qblock"><div class="qnum">Q7</div><div><div class="qtitle">ID3 Decision Tree Classification</div><div class="qsub">Information Gain · Entropy · Play Tennis dataset</div></div><span class="mbadge m6">6 Marks</span></div>
<div class="sec">📖 Concept</div>
<div class="understand"><div class="ul">What it means</div><p>ID3 (Iterative Dichotomiser 3) builds a decision tree by repeatedly splitting on the feature that gives the highest Information Gain (reduces entropy the most). Classic example: "Play Tennis" dataset — given weather conditions (outlook, humidity, wind), predict whether someone will play tennis.</p></div>
<div class="sec">💻 Python Program</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>ID3 Decision Tree — Play Tennis Dataset</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<div class="code"># ID3 Decision Tree Classification
# Dataset: Play Tennis (classic ML example)
# Features: Outlook, Temperature, Humidity, Wind → Predict: Play Tennis?

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier, export_text
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

# Step 1: Create Play Tennis Dataset
data = {
    'Outlook':     ['Sunny','Sunny','Overcast','Rain','Rain','Rain',
                    'Overcast','Sunny','Sunny','Rain','Sunny','Overcast',
                    'Overcast','Rain'],
    'Temperature': ['Hot','Hot','Hot','Mild','Cool','Cool','Cool',
                    'Mild','Cool','Mild','Mild','Mild','Hot','Mild'],
    'Humidity':    ['High','High','High','High','Normal','Normal','Normal',
                    'High','Normal','Normal','Normal','High','Normal','High'],
    'Wind':        ['Weak','Strong','Weak','Weak','Weak','Strong','Strong',
                    'Weak','Weak','Weak','Strong','Strong','Weak','Strong'],
    'PlayTennis':  ['No','No','Yes','Yes','Yes','No','Yes','No','Yes',
                    'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','No']
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print("Play Tennis Dataset:")
print(df.to_string(index=False))
print()

# Step 2: Encode categorical features to numbers
le = LabelEncoder()
df_encoded = df.copy()
for col in df.columns:
    df_encoded[col] = le.fit_transform(df[col])

X = df_encoded.drop('PlayTennis', axis=1)
y = df_encoded['PlayTennis']

# Step 3: Train ID3 Decision Tree (criterion='entropy' = ID3)
model = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy', random_state=42)
model.fit(X, y)

# Step 4: Print the Decision Tree
print("ID3 Decision Tree Structure:")
tree_rules = export_text(model, feature_names=list(X.columns))
print(tree_rules)

# Step 5: Evaluate
y_pred = model.predict(X)
accuracy = accuracy_score(y, y_pred)
print(f"Training Accuracy: {accuracy * 100:.2f}%")

# Step 6: Predict new sample
# Outlook=Sunny(2), Temp=Cool(0), Humidity=High(0), Wind=Weak(1)
new_sample = [[2, 0, 0, 1]]
prediction = model.predict(new_sample)
labels = ['No', 'Yes']
print(f"\nPrediction for Sunny, Cool, High Humidity, Weak Wind:")
print(f"  Play Tennis? → {labels[prediction[0]]}")</div>
